{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "e0a1f3b0-0000-4000-8000-c0a1f3b0e080",
    "name": "log-remediation-service (P9.3a anomaly read API)",
    "description": "Postman v2.1 collection for log-remediation-service on :8096 after P6.1a + P19/P20/P21 + P9.3/P9.3a. The service is primarily a Spring for Apache Kafka consumer that drains cortex.anomalies.v1, dedupes valid anomaly CloudEvents, runs fix-first remediation, emits cortex.remediation.outcomes.v1 audit events, and falls back to Slack/PagerDuty/Jira only when needed. P9.3a adds a direct tenant-scoped read API, GET /api/v1/anomalies?tenantId&since&until&limit, backed by the remediation-owned Postgres anomalies read model. Folder order: Admin asserts actuator + Prometheus exposition; Anomalies Read API asserts the P9.3a happy path and validation contract; Metrics-Baseline snapshots the dispatched_total{channel,outcome,tenant_id} counter for each channel; Channel-Mock-Smoke fires the WireMock-shaped POSTs that scripts/smoke-p6-1a.ps1 uses internally; Metrics-After verifies non-decreasing counters. For a seeded live read-model run, boot with scripts/live-e2e/smoke-p9-3a.ps1 -KeepInfra -KeepService, then run Newman with tenant_id and anomaly_event_id env vars printed by the smoke.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "if (!pm.variables.get('request_id')) {",
          "    pm.variables.set('request_id', 'pm-' + Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 12));",
          "}",
          "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Request-Id', value: pm.variables.get('request_id') });",
          "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Correlation-ID', value: pm.variables.get('request_id') });",
          "const tenant = pm.environment.get('tenant_id');",
          "if (tenant) { pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Tenant-Id', value: tenant }); }"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "pm.test('response under 15000 ms (actuator + mock-server tolerated)', function () {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(15000);",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
